message.content:
 To align a row of divs to the right using flex in CSS, follow these steps:

1. Add display: flex; property to the parent container (e.g., a div) to enable flexbox layout.
2. Set justify-content: flex-end; property on the parent container to align the items to the right edge of the container.

Here's an example:

HTML:
```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="item"></div>
  <div class="item"></div>
  <div class="item"></div>
</div>
```

CSS:
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: flex-end;
}

.item {
  background-color: blue;
  width: 50px;
  height: 50px;
  margin: 10px;
}
```
In this example, the `container` div will have all its child `item` divs aligned to the right.
